# Development Rules for Generic SaaS Project

## Backend (Django)
- Use session-based authentication instead of token-based for simplicity
- Always include CORS headers for frontend communication
- Use Django REST Framework for API endpoints
- Keep models simple and extensible
- Include useful comments for complex business logic
- Update requirements.txt when adding new packages

## Frontend (React + TypeScript)
- Use Zustand for state management instead of complex state libraries
- Pre-populate login forms with default credentials for development
- Use Tanstack Router for routing with proper authentication guards
- Display JSON data prominently in dashboard as requested
- Keep UI components simple and functional
- Use axios with credentials for API calls

## Database
- Use SQLite for development (simple to configure)
- Always run migrations after model changes
- Include starter data for development and testing
- Use management commands for data population

## Authentication Flow
- Frontend checks authentication status on app load
- Redirect unauthenticated users to login page
- Redirect authenticated users to dashboard
- Use Django sessions for authentication state
- Logout clears session and redirects to login

## API Structure
- /api/auth/login/ - POST for user login
- /api/auth/logout/ - POST for user logout  
- /api/auth/user/ - GET for current user info
- /api/customers/ - GET for customer list (JSON format)

## Development Workflow
- Start Django backend: python manage.py runserver
- Start frontend: npm run dev (Vite dev server on port 5173)
- Default credentials: admin/admin123 or demo/demo123
